###########################
#  Initialization

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"answerHints.pl",

"PGML.pl",
"PGcourse.pl",
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

###########################
#  Setup

Context("Numeric");
$t = random(3, 8);
$P = random(500, 900, 50);
$r = random(4, 8);
$ans = $P*$r*$t/100;

$rate = $r/100;


###########################
#  Main text

BEGIN_PGML
Find the simple interest earned after [$t] years on $[$P] at an interest rate of [$r]%.

[_________________]{$ans}

*Hint:  I = PRT*

END_PGML


############################
#  Solution

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
We can use the formula

*I = PRT*

to solve simple interest problems.

I = interest earned,
P = principal,
R = interest rate (as a decimal),
T = time (in years)

In this problem,

I = ?

P = [$P]

R = [$rate]

T = [$t]

If we plug those values into the formula, we get:

[`I = [$P]\cdot [$rate] \cdot [$t] = [$ans]`]

[`$[$ans]`] of interest is earned.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

COMMENT('MathObject version. Uses PGML.');

ENDDOCUMENT();